data.enText: to refuse to obey or show respect for sb in authority, a law, a rule, etc.

data.chText: 我可不敢不听老师的话。
data.enText: I wouldn't have dared to defy my teachers.

data.chText: 今天有数百人违抗禁止政治集会的规定。
data.enText: Hundreds of people today defied the ban on political gatherings.

data.chText: 不可能，无法（相信、解释、描绘等）
data.enText: to be impossible or almost impossible to believe, explain, describe, etc.
a political move that defies explanation

data.chText: 景色之美简直难以描绘。
data.enText: The beauty of the scene defies description.
to successfully resist sb/sth to a very unusual degree

data.chText: 这名男婴九死一生活了下来。
data.enText: The baby boy defied all the odds and survived (= stayed alive when it seemed certain that he would die) .
I defy you/anyone to do sth

data.chText: 激，挑动（某人尽力做你认为不可能的事）
data.enText: used to say that sb should try to do sth, as a way of emphasizing that you think it is impossible to do it

data.chText: 我倒要看看有谁在电影结尾时不哭。
data.enText: I defy anyone not to cry at the end of the film.

means: 不可能，无法(相信、解释、描绘等)

ex.chText: 那些公然蔑视法律的人已经受到了严惩。
ex.enText: Those who openly defy the law have been severely punished.

ex.chText: 他不允许任何人挑衅他的管理权威。
ex.enText: He won't allow anyone to defy his managerial authority.

synonyms.bx: 指违抗法律或规则，也可以指拒不服从有权威者。

ex.chText: 他不听老师的话，在课堂上看小说。
ex.enText: He disobeyed his teacher and read novels in class.

ex.chText: 那个人不遵守交通规则。
ex.enText: That man disobeyed the traffic rules.
Those who disobey cannot escape punishment.

synonyms.bx: 指不服从上级命令或不遵守法律、规定等。

ex.chText: 一些公司公然违反规定，贿赂高官。
ex.enText: Some companies flouted the rules and bribed officials of high rank.

ex.chText: 行人经常无视交通法规。
ex.enText: Pedestrians often flout the traffic law.

synonyms.bx: 指公然违抗法律、规定、纪律等。

data.enText: I defy you/anyone to do sth

data.chText: 激，挑动（某人尽力做你认为不可能的事）
data.enText: used to say that sb should try to do sth, as a way of emphasizing that you think it is impossible to do it

data.chText: 我倒要看看有谁在电影结尾时不哭。
data.enText: I defy anyone not to cry at the end of the film.

example: The new material withstands even the greatest wear and tear

tr: elude, especially in a baffling way

value.def: If you defy someone or something that is trying to make you behave in a particular way, you refuse to obey them and behave in that way.

example.ex: This was the first (and last) time that I dared to defy my mother...
example.tran: 这是我第一次(也是最后一次)胆敢反抗我的母亲。

example.ex: Nearly eleven-thousand people have been arrested for defying the ban on street trading.
example.tran: 将近有1.1万人因为违抗禁止在街上摆摊交易的禁令而被捕。

value.def: If you defy someone to do something, you challenge them to do it when you think that they will be unable to do it or too frightened to do it.

example.ex: I defy you to come up with one major accomplishment of the current Prime Minister...
example.tran: 我敢说你讲不出现任首相的哪怕一项重大成就。

example.ex: He looked at me as if he was defying me to argue.
example.tran: 他看着我，仿佛在激我与他争论。

value.tran: 挑战;激;认为…不敢(或无法)（做）

value.def: If something defies description or understanding, it is so strange, extreme, or surprising that it is almost impossible to understand or explain.

example.ex: When the flowers open in spring they fill the night air with a fragrance that defies description...
example.tran: 春天鲜花开放时，夜里的空气中会弥漫一种难以名状的香气。

example.ex: It's a devastating and barbaric act that defies all comprehension.
example.tran: 这种行为野蛮凶残、令人震惊，简直是不可理喻。

value.def: If you say that someone defies their age, or defies the years, you mean that their appearance or behaviour suggests that they are younger than they really are.

example.ex: The singer continues to defy her age by wearing the scantiest of outfits.
example.tran: 那名女歌手依旧穿着非常暴露的服装，完全不似她这把岁数。
